OL,3,CUtility companies dug up NI roads
OL,4,C55,000 times in a year, report finds
OL,6,F"While road openings by utilities are
OL,7,Fcertainly not the sole cause of
OL,8,Fdeteriorations in the network, they
OL,9,Fare potentially a contributing factor
OL,10,Fadding to this significant financial
OL,11,Fburden."
OL,13,F"Given the growing number of road
OL,14,Fopenings, and the department's failure
OL,15,Fto meet its existing inspection and
OL,16,Ftesting targets, it is vital that
OL,17,Fresources which are available are
OL,18,Futilised to deliver the most benefit.
