OL,3,CUtility companies dug up NI roads
OL,4,C55,000 times in a year, report finds
OL,6,F"Therefore, the report recommends that
OL,7,Fthe department considers introducing
OL,8,Frisk-based sampling for inspections,
OL,9,Fand whether increased allocation of
OL,10,Fresources to more detailed core
OL,11,Ftesting might deliver better value to
OL,12,Ftaxpayers."
OL,14,FThe report also recommends that the
OL,15,Fdepartment considers whether the
OL,16,Fcurrent warranty period in Northern
OL,17,FIreland is adequate for protecting
OL,18,Ftaxpayers from costs relating to
OL,19,Fdefective reinstatements by utility
OL,20,Fcompanies.
